## 5. Brand System Summary

The OPRMT™ visual system should communicate:

```text
structured
technical
professional
governed
precise
credible
framework-oriented
implementation-ready
```

The preferred brand identity uses:

```text
Dark navy
Deep blue
Framework gold
White
Neutral grays
Clean sans-serif typography
Monospace formatting for prompts and code
Structured spacing
High contrast
Minimal visual noise
```

---

## 6. Primary Color Reference

Use the full guide in:

```text
assets/brand/BRAND_COLORS.md
```

Primary palette:

| Role | Color | Hex |
|---|---|---:|
| Primary Background | OPRMT Navy | `#071A2F` |
| Secondary Background | Deep System Blue | `#0B2545` |
| Accent | Framework Gold | `#D6A84F` |
| Primary Light Text | Clean White | `#FFFFFF` |
| Light Background | Soft White | `#F7F9FC` |
| Body Text | Slate Gray | `#334155` |
| Muted Text | Muted Gray | `#64748B` |
| Borders | Border Gray | `#CBD5E1` |

---

## 7. Typography Reference

Use the full guide in:

```text
assets/brand/TYPOGRAPHY.md
```

Recommended sans-serif font stack:

```css
font-family: Inter, Aptos, "Source Sans 3", "Helvetica Neue", Arial, sans-serif;
```

Recommended monospace font stack:

```css
font-family: "JetBrains Mono", "IBM Plex Mono", "Source Code Pro", SFMono-Regular, Consolas, "Courier New", monospace;
```

Use monospace fonts for:

- Prompt templates
- Variables
- Repository paths
- Code blocks
- YAML
- JSON
- CLI commands
- File trees

---

## 8. Brand Usage Reference

Use the full guide in:

```text
assets/brand/USAGE_GUIDELINES.md
```

Correct naming:

```text
OPRMT™
OPRMT™ Framework
The OPRMT™ Framework
OPRMT™ structured prompt framework
```

Correct framework sequence:

```text
O — Objective
P — Parameters
R — Results
M — Method
T — Tools
```

Attribution:

```text
OPRMT™ Framework created by Michael W. Fleming.
```

---

## 9. File Naming Rules

Brand files should use clear, readable names.

Preferred examples:

```text
OPRMT-Logo-Primary.svg
OPRMT-Logo-White.svg
OPRMT-Framework-Flow.svg
OPRMT-PCE-Validation-Flow.svg
OPRMT-DOAS-Scoring-Flow.svg
OPRMT-PDF-Cover-Template.png
OPRMT-Slide-Cover-Template.png
```

Avoid:

```text
logo-final.png
new-logo.png
image1.png
copy-of-logo.svg
final-final-logo.png
random-brand-thing.png
```

---

## 10. Asset Format Guidance

Recommended formats:

| Asset Type | Preferred Format | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Logos | SVG | Use vector format where possible |
| Icons | SVG | Keep scalable and editable |
| Diagrams | SVG or PNG | SVG preferred for documentation |
| PDF covers | PNG or SVG | Use high-resolution exports |
| Slide graphics | PNG or SVG | Keep text readable |
| Product mockups | PNG | Use transparent background where appropriate |
| Editable design files | Canva, Figma, or source file | Store externally or document location if not stored in repo |

Avoid storing unnecessarily large files in the repository unless required.

---

## 11. Logo Asset Rules

When official logo files are added:

- Preserve original proportions.
- Do not stretch or distort.
- Do not recolor outside approved palette.
- Do not place on low-contrast backgrounds.
- Do not remove ownership or trademark references.
- Do not use the logo to imply official authorization without permission.
- Do not combine with third-party marks in a way that implies partnership.

Recommended future file:

```text
assets/brand/LOGO_USAGE.md
```

---

## 12. Diagram Asset Rules

Diagrams should use the OPRMT™ visual system.

Recommended diagram style:

```text
Background: White or Soft White
Primary nodes: OPRMT Navy
Secondary nodes: Deep System Blue
Accent lines: Framework Gold
Body text: Slate Gray
Labels: Clean, short, technical
Layout: Structured, grid-based
```

Avoid:

- Overloaded diagrams
- Excessive colors
- Cartoon graphics
- Unlabeled arrows
- Decorative icons that reduce clarity
- Low-contrast labels

---

## 13. Badge Asset Rules

Badges should be used for repository documentation, specification markers, and visual categorization.

Potential badge categories:

```text
OPRMT™ Framework
PCE
DOAS™
Specification
Draft
Approved
Deprecated
Prompt Template
Prompt Cluster
Certification Support
Repository Governance
```

Badges must not imply certification, accreditation, legal recognition, or official approval unless specifically authorized.

---

## 14. Product Image Rules

Product images should maintain a professional technical style.

Recommended product image traits:

- Dark navy and white foundation
- Gold accent lines or labels
- Clean mockups
- Structured dashboard visuals
- Prompt interface previews
- High contrast
- Corporate SaaS tone
- No cluttered backgrounds
- No exaggerated income claims
- No unsupported guarantee language

Product mockups should not imply official certification, legal recognition, or guaranteed results unless verified and approved.

---

## 15. PDF and Slide Asset Rules

PDF and slide templates should follow the approved color and typography system.

Recommended PDF structure:

```text
Cover
Document metadata
Purpose
Main sections
Tables and structured blocks
Implementation notes
Ownership notice
Footer
```

Recommended slide structure:

```text
Cover slide
Section divider
Framework explanation
Component breakdown
Example
Review checklist
Ownership notice
```

---

## 16. Contribution Rules for Brand Assets

Before adding brand assets:

- Confirm the asset belongs in `assets/brand/`.
- Use approved naming conventions.
- Use approved colors.
- Use approved typography.
- Add a README if creating a new subfolder.
- Avoid unsupported claims.
- Preserve ownership notices.
- Use vector formats where practical.
- Optimize file size where possible.
- Submit changes through pull request review.
- Update `BRAND_ASSET_INVENTORY.md` if that file exists.

---

## 17. Review Checklist

Use this checklist before approving brand assets.

- [ ] File name is clear and repository-appropriate.
- [ ] Asset uses approved brand colors.
- [ ] Asset uses approved typography.
- [ ] Text is readable.
- [ ] Asset does not distort the logo.
- [ ] Asset does not imply unauthorized certification or endorsement.
- [ ] Asset does not contain unsupported claims.
- [ ] Asset includes or preserves ownership context where applicable.
- [ ] Asset format is appropriate.
- [ ] Asset size is reasonable.
- [ ] Related README or inventory file is updated.

---

## 18. Commercial Use Warning

Repository visibility does not automatically grant commercial-use rights.

Before using OPRMT™ brand assets commercially, review:

```text
LICENSE.md
NOTICE.md
legal/COMMERCIAL_USE_GUIDANCE.md
legal/USAGE_POLICY.md
legal/COMMERCIAL_USE_POLICY.md
```

Commercial use may require written permission.

Restricted commercial uses may include:

- Selling OPRMT™ branded products
- Using OPRMT™ marks in client deliverables
- Creating paid OPRMT™ courses
- Claiming official certification authority
- Using OPRMT™ brand assets in commercial software
- White-labeling OPRMT™ materials
- Removing ownership notices

